- [docs/Algorithms_In_Strategy_Context.md](docs/Algorithms_In_Strategy_Context.md)
- [docs/rulesets_v1.md](docs/rulesets_v1.md)

### 5.2 wheel

- Intent: lane-aware wheel lifecycle management across opener and follow-on contexts.
- Supports active-instance and generic-new-lane recommendation behavior with explicit semantics.
- ALT CC policy block (`alt_cc`) exists in policy template and supports regime-aware ranking controls.
- Multi-instance same-symbol behavior and lineage mapping are now core operational concerns.
- Within the `wheel` strategy, multiple separate active lineages can coexist and are distinguished by numbered instances in console output.
- Lanes are lifecycle lineages in either trade_mode; `real` and `paper` partition those lanes but do not redefine what a lane is.

